Screenings & Covid Precautions

  • When you arrive Saturday, your entire traveling party will report to the purple tent by the soccer practice field where team camps will be set up. Attached you will find an Asbury Health Screening form for all athletes, coaches and staff. You can have this filled out and signed by a trainer before you leave your school Saturday morning, then turn it in to our Athletic Training staff when you arrive at Asbury. All of your athletes and coaches still must do a temperature check when you arrive, but you will not have to answer all of the screen questions if the form is filled out. If you expect to arrive before 9:45am, please let Coach Crist know (859-351-4653).

  • If you are unable to meet with your trainer Saturday morning then please have the names already filled out on the form, and our trainer will conduct the screening when you arrive at Asbury.

  • If you are coming to Asbury Friday afternoon to run the course, then you do need to be screened by your trainer before you travel and you can bring your signed screening form. Your athletes WILL have to be screened again Saturday morning, either by your own trainer or the Asbury training staff. Please have your team names already filled in on the form before you hand it to the trainer.

  • Athletes, Coaches, and Staff must wear face masks at all times, except for athletes actively warming up or while competing. Athletes should return to team camps immediately following their race and put their masks back on

  • Team camps should be set up a reasonable distance from each other on the soccer practice field.

  • Report to the starting line 5 minutes before your race (not sooner). Know your starting box before you come to the line; there will not be a clerk. Box 1 is the end nearer the softball field. Your starting box is only 5 wide to allow for spacing between teams, so larger teams may have to plan ahead for how your athletes will arrange themselves.

  • Instruct your athletes to run past the finish line and quickly clear the finish line area. They should return immediately to your team camp area. Early finishers should not walk back along the course to cheer teammates in the homestretch.

  • We will not be distributing water to athletes at the finish each team should plan to have water at your team camp area.

  • There will not be an awards ceremony. After results are posted online, one coach should come to the awards table to pick up team or individual awards (1st & 2nd place team trophies, top 20 individual awards).

  • All parents and other spectators must wear masks and should position themselves on or near the lacrosse field. They can see a great deal of the race from there. They should NOT be on the soccer practice field were the team camps are located. They should NOT be anywhere near the start or finish areas. They should NOT line up along the edge of the course to cheer on their team. Please help us enforce this by telling your own team fans where they should and shouldnt be.

  • Portable toilets will be available for athletes and spectators. They may also go into the Luce Center for the restrooms or public locker rooms, but if they do go inside, they MUST enter through the front doors of the building, MUST be wearing a mask, and MUST have their temperature taken by the worker at the front desk.
